description: The island has had no cases for 28 days and has achieved "local elimination", the chief minister says.
title: Coronavirus: Isle of Man achieves 'local elimination' of Covid-19
title_page: Coronavirus: Isle of Man achieves 'local elimination' of Covid-19 - BBC News
maintext: Howard Quayle said having no new cases for 28 days was a "line in the sand" and, at times, it had been "hard to imagine when this day might arrive".
